-- Henderson Land Said to Increase Syndicated Loan by 66% to HK$13.25 Billion
-- Katrina Nicholas
-- 2010-06-23T09:24:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/henderson-land-said-to-increase-syndicated-loan-by-66-to-hk-13-25-billion.html

          
          
             Henderson Land Development Co .,
controlled by Hong Kong billionaire  Lee Shau-kee , increased a
loan to HK$13.25 billion ($1.7 billion) from HK$8 billion after
banks offered more than it initially sought, according to a
person familiar with the matter.  
 The company will sign an agreement with 18 banks on June 28
for a five-year loan, the person said, asking not to be
identified as the details are private.  
 Henderson Landâ€™s facility is split between a revolving loan
and a term loan, and lenders that pledged at least HK$1.5
billion will get interest of 89 basis points more than the  Hong
Kong interbank offered rate , another person said on June 18.  
 The lenders are Australia  New Zealand Banking Group Ltd.,
Bank of East Asia Ltd., Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd., Bank
of China (Hong Kong) Ltd., China Merchants Bank Ltd., ING Groep
NV, HSBC Holdings Plc, Mizuho Financial Group Inc., Sumitomo
Mitsui Banking Corp., United Overseas Bank Ltd., DBS Group
Holdings Ltd., Credit Agricole CIB, Chong Hing Bank Ltd., Hang
Seng Bank Ltd., Oversea-Chinese Banking Corp., Royal Bank of
Scotland Group Plc, Standard Chartered Plc and Shanghai
Commercial  Savings Bank Ltd., the first person said.  
